website=ESPN.com|access-date=February 8, 2019}}</ref> and had the second best class behind [[2019 Georgia Bulldogs football team|Georgia]] according to [[Rivals.com]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://n.rivals.com/team_rankings/2019/all-teams/football|title=2019 team rankings|website=Rivals.com|access-date=February 8, 2019}}</ref> The class was ranked No. 1 by the 247Sports Composite, which aggregates the ratings of the major recruiting services.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://247sports.com/Season/2019-Football/CompositeTeamRankings/|title=2019 Football Team Rankings [Composite]|website=247Sports.com|access-date=February 8, 2019}}</ref> Headlining the class were consensus top-10 recruits Antonio Alfano (defensive end), Trey Sanders (running back), and Evan Neal (offensive tackle).\n{{College athlete recruit start|40=No|collapse=yes|year=2019}}\n{{College athlete recruit entry \n| recruit = Antonio Alfano\n| position = DT         \n| hometown = [[Colonia, New Jersey]]          \n| highschool = [[Colonia High School]]                         \n| feet      = 6                   \n| inches    = 4          \n| weight    = 275     \n| commitdate = May 18, 2018                    \n| rivals stars = 5          \n| 247 stars    = 5               \n| espn grade   = 86    \n| espn stars   = 4               \n}}\n{{College athlete recruit entry \n| recruit = Marcus Banks\n| position = CB\n| hometown = [[Houston, Texas]]          \n| highschool = [[Andy Dekaney High School]]                         \n| feet      = 6                   \n| inches    = 0\n| weight    = 166\n| commitdate = January 5, 2019                 \n| rivals stars = 4          \n| 247 stars    = 4               \n| espn grade   = 81  \n| espn stars   = 4               \n}}\n{{College athlete recruit entry \n| recruit = Jordan Battle\n| position = S        \n| hometown = [[Fort Lauderdale, Florida]]          \n| highschool = [[St. Thomas Aquinas High School (Florida)|Saint Thomas Aquinas High School]]                   