ter\n| Senior \n| Defensive back \n|-\n| Xavier McKinney\n| Junior \n| Defensive back  \n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"  style=\"font-size:8pt; text-align:center;\"|'''Reference:'''\n|}\n\n{{Col-3}}\n'''Special Teams'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Player\n! Class\n! Position\n|-\n| Joseph Bulovas\n| RS Sophomore \n| Placekicker \n|-\n| Trevon Diggs\n| Senior \n| Kick Returner\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\"  style=\"font-size:8pt; text-align:right;\"|'''Reference:'''\n|}\n{{Col-end}}\n{{citation needed|date=July 2019}}\n\n===Spring game===\nThe 2019 Crimson Tide held spring practices in March and April. The 2019 Alabama football spring game, \"A-Day\" took place in [[Tuscaloosa, Alabama|Tuscaloosa, AL]] on April 13, 2019, at 1 p.m. [[Central Time Zone|CST]] with the White team beating the Crimson team 31\u201317. Freshman WR John Metchie was named A-Day MVP after hauling in five catches for a game-high 133 receiving yards. White team QB [[Mac Jones]] led all passers, completing 19 of 23 passes for 271 yards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://247sports.com/college/alabama/Article/Recap-White-team-tops-Crimson-in-Alabama-Footballs-2019-A-Day-Game-131173380/|title=Recap: White team tops Crimson in Alabama's 2019 A-Day Game|first=Charlie|last=Potter|website=BamaOnLine|publisher=247Sports|date=April 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Preseason==\n===Award watch lists=== \n<small>Listed in the order that they were released</small>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Alabama Crimson Tide|Award|Player|Position|Year}}\n|-\n|[[Lott Trophy]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lottimpacttrophy.org/2019-watch-list/|title=2019 LOTT IMPACT TROPHY WATCH LIST CANDIDATES - Lott IMPACT Trophy|publisher=}}</ref>\n|[[Dylan Moses]]\n|LB\n|JR\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[Maxwell Award]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.maxwellfootballclub.org/2019-maxwell-award-watch-list/|title=2019 Maxwell Award Watch List - Maxwell Football Club|date=15 July 2019|publisher=}}</ref>\n|[[Tua Tagovailoa]]\n|QB\n|JR\n|-\n|[[Najee Harris]]\n|RB\n|J